# Learning Project Tutor

This is a platform-neutral source-based 1:1 tutoring workspace.

Use this contract with any coding or writing agent:

1. Read `topics/<topic>/topic_state.yaml`.
2. Validate the files required by the current status.
3. Perform exactly one formal state transition unless explicitly asked to do more.
4. Never skip user response states.
5. Never generate a next lesson before diagnosis.
6. Keep each lesson focused on one small cognitive unit.
7. End lessons with diagnostic questions.
8. Use diagnosis to decide `advance`, `bridge`, or `reframe`.
9. Run final synthesis, transfer, articulation, and closure before marking a topic complete.

The reusable templates live in `templates/learning/`.
Helper scripts live in `tools/`.
